body_html:
I mainly encountered 2 issues.

  1. "duplicate symbol" issue:
    duplicate symbol __ZN10tensorflow15CreateGPUTracerEv in: /Users/XXXX/tensorflow-master/tensorflow/contrib/makefile/gen/lib/libtensorflow-core.a(gpu_tracer.o) ld: 1 duplicate symbol for architecture arm64
    I solved this by commenting the gpu_tracker.cc line in Makefile. I don't know the side effect of this operation.
  2. "No OpKernel was registered to support Op XXX" issue
    I solve this by following the above link. I finally recompiled a library that contained all ops of my model, as it listed in my ops_to_registered.h.

Hope that you can solve your problem soon. =^_^=

body:
I mainly encountered 2 issues. 
1. "duplicate symbol" issue:
`duplicate symbol __ZN10tensorflow15CreateGPUTracerEv in:
    /Users/XXXX/tensorflow-master/tensorflow/contrib/makefile/gen/lib/libtensorflow-core.a(gpu_tracer.o)
ld: 1 duplicate symbol for architecture arm64`
I solved this by commenting the gpu_tracker.cc line in Makefile. I don't know the side effect of this operation.
2. "No OpKernel was registered to support Op XXX" issue
I solve this by following the above link. I finally recompiled a library that contained all ops of my model, as it listed in my ops_to_registered.h. 

Hope that you can solve your problem soon. =^_^=
